{
    "description_long": "This newspaper stand is a small, rectangular concrete structure with a weathered, gray exterior and a flat roof. The front features a red door with a yellow warning sign in Arabic, and a large black-framed display window partially filled with newspapers and flyers. A wooden ladder is attached to one side, providing access to the roof, while the opposite side is plain and unadorned. The back of the stand is featureless, and the roof is bordered by dark, low walls on two sides, possibly for added security or display. Various posters, papers, and graffiti are visible on the front, adding to its urban, well-used appearance. The overall look suggests a robust, utilitarian design suitable for busy city streets.",
